  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air, then boil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>bulgur wheat</strong> to a pot with plenty of<strong> boiled water </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook over a high heat for 7-9 min or until tender with a slight bite, then drain and return to the pot</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/438__-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/438__-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/438__-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/438__-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/438__-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>walnuts</strong> and toast for 3-4 min, or until they've darkened in colour slightly</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/438__-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/438__-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/438__-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/438__-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/438__-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the walnuts are toasting, chop your <strong>basil</strong> coarsely (including the stalks)</p><p>Peel and roughly chop your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Crumble your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong> into small pieces</p><p>Transfer the <strong>toasted walnuts</strong> to a <strong>food processor</strong> and reserve the pan for later</p><p>Tip: If you don't have a food processor, chop the walnuts with a knife, then add to a pestle & mortar!</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/438__-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/438__-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/438__-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
